#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""noti — tiny toast prompts + turn summaries for Claude Code (and any agent).

REUSABLE PRIMITIVES (any script/agent can call these):
    noti ask    --title T --message M --buttons Yes,Always,No
        Shows a blocking corner toast. Prints the clicked label to stdout;
        exit code is the button index (0-based), or 124 on timeout.
    noti notify --title T --body B
        Shows a non-blocking summary toast that auto-dismisses. Returns at once.

CLAUDE CODE HOOK ADAPTER (wired up by `noti install`):
    noti hook pretooluse   # reads PreToolUse JSON on stdin -> permission decision
    noti hook stop         # reads Stop JSON on stdin -> end-of-turn summary toast
    noti decide            # dry-run: print the policy decision, never show a toast

SETUP:
    noti build | install [--global|--project DIR] | uninstall | doctor | version

Everything is dependency-free stdlib Python 3 + one tiny Swift binary (bin/noti-toast).
Design rule #1: a bug in here must NEVER block your Claude Code session. Every hook
path is wrapped so that on any error we emit no decision (exit 0) and let Claude's
own permission flow take over.
"""

